# DONE — Telegram outbound producer audit

Current in-tree source only. No files changed, no tests run, no commit.

## 1. `gateway/send.message` producers

Every event goes through:

`gateway/send.message` → `packages/system-bus/src/inngest/functions/gateway-send-message.ts:22-65` → `joelclaw:outbound:messages` → `packages/gateway/src/daemon.ts:4993-5160` → Telegram adapter.

The event contract at `packages/system-bus/src/inngest/client.ts:1214-1228` has **no priority, importance, urgency, or classification field**.

| Producer | File:line | Content | Attribution |
|---|---|---|---|
| Daily token usage report | `packages/system-bus/src/inngest/functions/daily-token-usage-report.ts:353-359` | Scheduled usage/cost report | Explicit: `daily-token-usage-report` |
| NAS retry budget exhausted | `packages/system-bus/src/inngest/functions/nas-backup.ts:1731-1743` | Infra failure escalation | Explicit: `nas-backup-retry-budget` |
| NAS escalation | `packages/system-bus/src/inngest/functions/nas-backup.ts:1795-1807` | Infra failure escalation | Explicit: `nas-backup-escalation` |
| ADR daily pitch | `packages/system-bus/src/inngest/functions/adr-daily-pitch.ts:362-379` | Joel action with buttons | Explicit: `adr-daily-pitch` |
| ADR approved edit | `packages/system-bus/src/inngest/functions/adr-daily-pitch.ts:439-448` | Action receipt/message edit | Explicit: `adr-pitch-approved` |
| ADR rejected edit | `packages/system-bus/src/inngest/functions/adr-daily-pitch.ts:470-479` | Action receipt/message edit | Explicit: `adr-pitch-rejected` |
| Queue observer report | `packages/system-bus/src/inngest/functions/queue-observer.ts:834-842` | Queue remediation/escalation report | Explicit: `queue-observer` |
| Wiki morning receipt | `packages/system-bus/src/inngest/functions/wiki-edition-build.ts:221-224` | Routine success receipt | **Generic:** `gateway/send.message` |
| Wiki failed/blocked receipt | `packages/system-bus/src/inngest/functions/wiki-edition-build.ts:227-235` | Build failure/blockage | **Generic:** `gateway/send.message` |
| Self-healing backup blocked | `packages/system-bus/src/inngest/functions/self-healing-router.ts:763-778` | Safety escalation | Explicit: `self-healing-backup-blocked` |
| Self-healing retry exhausted | `packages/system-bus/src/inngest/functions/self-healing-router.ts:847-865` | Retry/route failure | Explicit: `self-healing-retry-exhausted` |
| Self-healing escalated | `packages/system-bus/src/inngest/functions/self-healing-router.ts:979-994` | Verified escalation candidate | Explicit: `self-healing-escalated` |

`buildQueuedGatewayMessage()` at `packages/system-bus/src/lib/channel-delivery-audit.ts:24-59` adds `flowId`, timestamps, host identity, and content fingerprint. Missing producer names collapse to `gateway/send.message`.

## 2. `joelclaw notify send`

### Runtime callers

| Producer | File:line | Content | Priority | Attribution |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Voice verification | `infra/voice-agent/verify-voice.sh:168` | Raw probe failure | `urgent` | `cli/notify` |
| SMS campaign vetting | `infra/voice-agent/sms-campaign-vetting-check.sh:25,55,60` | Campaign failure/success | `normal` | `cli/notify` |
| Satellite health/repair | `packages/cli/src/commands/satellite.ts:67-128` | Infra repair request | Default `high` | Explicit: `satellite-health` |
| Contact-enrichment DAG | `packages/restate/src/trigger-dag.ts:345-355` | Completion receipt | `normal` | `cli/notify` |
| SDK public entrypoint | `packages/sdk/src/client.ts:319-365` | Arbitrary caller-supplied notification | Caller supplied | Source or `cli/notify` |

The actual adapter is `packages/sdk/src/capabilities/adapters/gateway-redis.ts:129-231`.

It maps:

- `low|normal` → `level: info`
- `high` → `level: warn`, `immediateTelegram: true`
- `urgent` → `level: fatal`, `immediateTelegram: true`
- `--telegram-only` → remove from the later agent-prompt lane after direct delivery

It creates a real audit at `gateway-redis.ts:143-148` with `flowId: notify:<UUID>` and `producer: source`.

### Protocol-equivalent Restate producer

`packages/restate/src/otel.ts:82-143` writes the same Redis event shape without using the CLI.

| Caller | File:line | Content | Priority | Attribution |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| DAG planning failure | `packages/restate/src/workflows/dag-orchestrator.ts:578-586` | Infra/workflow failure | `high` | Event source `restate/dag`; no audit seed |
| DAG execution failure | `packages/restate/src/workflows/dag-orchestrator.ts:707-725` | Infra/workflow failure | `high` | Same |
| DAG completion | `packages/restate/src/workflows/dag-orchestrator.ts:787-808` | Routine completion | `normal` | Same |

The gateway reconstructs attribution from `event.source` for immediate delivery, but the original event lacks a `ChannelDeliveryAudit`.

